Package: osgeo0
Title: R Interface to the GDAL Geographic Network Model (osgeo.gnm)
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Michael", "Sumner", , "mdsumner@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Idiomatic R bindings for the GDAL Geographic Network Model 
    (GNM) via the Python osgeo.gnm module and reticulate. Create, manage, 
    and analyse geographic networks (water pipes, roads, electrical grids) 
    with topology building, shortest-path analysis, and connected component 
    detection. Uses wk for geometry interchange and S7 for the class system. 
    Designed as a template for broader osgeo.* wrapping in R.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/mdsumner/osgeo0
BugReports: https://github.com/mdsumner/osgeo0/issues
Imports:
    cli,
    reticulate,
    S7,
    wk
Suggests:
    gdalraster,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    withr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/reticulate:
  list(
    packages = list(
      list(package = "gdal", pip = FALSE, channel = "conda-forge")
    )
  )
